roup members, and the other was composed primarily of Wood Elven Rangers but also had a Dark Elven Shadowknight in the group.  (It actually turned out that the &quot;Dark Elf&quot; in the group with the  High Elf was actually a Gnomish Rogue using one of them mask thingies, but the one with the Wood Elven Rangers was not.)<br><br>I see High Elves and Wood Elves regularly grouped with Dark Elves in the Great Divide, as well, and I'm sure they all (the &quot;good&quot; characters and the &quot;evil&quot; characters alike) have really good &quot;roleplay&quot; reasons for their actions.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Over the past few weeks, I've gotten asked for Spirit of Wolf by random people either when I teleport into a Druid Ring somewhere, or when I was waiting for the Spires to send me to the Nexus.  When I would turn around (or, sometimes, cast See Invisibility), I'd discover that the person saying &quot;Bro, sow plz&quot; was a Dark Elf.  This has happened about once every three or four teleports I do, and has even happened when I'm on a corpse-recovery.  Some of them have gotten mad at me for responding in-character: &quot;Teir'Dal scum, why shouldn't I slay you on the spot?&quot;<br><br>An expectation has been set up that if you refuse to aid or group with those who are known to be your character's race's sworn enemies, that you're the &quot;jerk&quot; or some kind of &quot;roleplay police&quot;.  This is the same expectation that exists on blue servers.<br><br>When the alignment rules were in place, this expectation did not exist.  Good characters simply couldn't help evil characters, and vice-versa, and people knew not to ask.<br><br>Convenience takes precedence over roleplay. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>-Monique Wittig, "The Straight Mind"<BR>andersonrob@earthlink.net<BR>http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/index.html<BR>AIM: RWAnderson<BR>ICQ: 43988595<BR>EverQuest: Lasgalen Lothir of Lux Aeternam, Firiona Vie server<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 8/16/02 2:56:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 929<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 2:49:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> Yeah, something like that. Best thing to do is not help them. <p><A HREF="http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/sageofthehalo/"><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif"></A><BR>Shintou is killing Woodelves.<BR>All's right with the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utitaisia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Titaisia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wishful Dreamer</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 2:52:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> ((*sigh*  *agree*)) <p>Captain Titaisia Lightheart<BR>