y &quot;allied&quot; cities (Kelethin, Kaladim, Felwithe, Rivervale, Ak'Anon) then they are worth my consideration.  As a result, there are only two evils that I will work with - Cronadan and Siava, both of Twilight Bastion.<br><br>I'm busting my skinny elven butt to get into and out of Cabilis alive... I know the effort faction work takes.  If a player puts forth that kind of grind into making their character break the mold, then I'm not going to punish them for HAVING to choose neutral evil instead of neutral neutral.<br><br>That said, it'd take an act of sheer desperation to group with or accept aid from a necromancer or shadowknight.  That, to me, goes beyond a matter of alignment and into a far more cosmic matter of disrupting the Cycle.<br><br>But, again, as a neutral follower of Karana, I tend to assume most people are deserving of aid and shelter until they prove me wrong.  After that, they're SOL.<br><br>My 2cp only.  You can throw rocks at me when you see me in game if you want.<br><br>(edit - cleaned up some gibberish and made some clarifications) <p><div align="center"><b>Uinin Stormsong</b><br>Bard of the Ledenyetz Troupe<br>Herald of Karana<br>~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268592">My Current Playlist</a> ~</div></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A> at: 8/16/02 3:08:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 678<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:14:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> Maybe you missed the finer point I was making.<br><br>EVERYONE's an outcast.  EVERYONE's an exile.  EVERYONE's a non-conformist.<br><br>When it suits them, that is.<br><br>Maybe you missed the quotation marks around &quot;roleplay&quot;, or the implication that I simply don't believe most of the lame &quot;roleplay&quot; reasons people give--I think 90% of them are disingenuous, and, as implied above, the real reason for these groups is convenience, not &quot;roleplay'. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>-Monique Wittig, "The Straight Mind"<BR>andersonrob@earthlink.net<BR>http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/index.html<BR>AIM: RWAnderson<BR>ICQ: 43988595<BR>EverQuest: Lasgalen Lothir of Lux Aeternam, Firiona Vie server<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 407<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:16:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> There's a distinction... not every one of the outcasts has worked for weeks on end to be accepted in lighty cities and even destroyed their darkie faction. <br><br>That is very different than just *saying* you are an outcast. <p><br><imgsrc="http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/ISHARR6.jpg"><br><b><br><b>Property of Voskor Oth</b><br><b>Slave to the Iksar Empire</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubobmato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobmato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:26:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> I really wish they would reinstate alignments (and grouping restrictions) and have them fluid based on various faction changes. Raising faction with certain groups should have an effect on your alignment.<br><br>Also have various caps on faction for varous classes, and gods (not races).  For example, a paladin should never get any better then dubious toward The Dead, no matter what faction work he does.  A Necro should never be more than dubious to Keepers of the Art. And you should be able to quest to change your god too.  (the Dark Elf  warrior who turns from Innorruuk and builds the trust of the wood elfs could learn to worship Tunare)<br><br>That would work more toward RP alignments.  At least better than the way it was and how it is now.  And maybe we would loose a few d00dz.<br><br>~Bobmato<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 959<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> Okay, let's be honest though.  In a lot of cases, the &quot;work&quot; in raising a faction involves giving some NPC a ton of wine and/or bonechips, or setting off a few well placed AE spells in a newbie dungeon.  But as you said, I would respect a Dark elf outcast more, as an example, if not only did they raise their faction with the elves to acceptance, but trashed their dark elf reputation such that they could no longer enter Neriak.<br><br>Grobb and Oggok are probably the only places that make you really work to boost your faction there.  <br><br>In roleplaying, everyone likes to feel their character is unique.  Set against the backdrop of Norrath, it seems easiest to make your character stand out by going in a different direction than the NPC populace.  The psycopathic wood elf... the heroic dark elf... the law abiding halfing... the sexually repressed gnome... <br><br>The problem is so many people go that route, it almost seems more unusual to find characters staying true to the background of their race (ie: Paladins that want to clash with shadowknights -vs- just feeling pity on them, sadistic evil dark elves, etc).  The Iksar on the server are probably the only race that tends to stay true to their background, and a lot of that comes from internal censure (there's a lot of PC Iksar that will insult the hell out of you for associating with softskins).<br><br>That might be blowing the situation out of proportion, but the problems Lasgalen sees are definately there.  The &quot;Everyone's an outcast&quot; problem, that is.<br><br>I swear I would pay to see a Paladin say to someone &quot;I take no pleasure in this act, but for the greater good I must lay you to rest&quot; rather than &quot;I will not draw my blade for I pity you.  Perhaps, Hungry_Ogre03 if you travel with me you will learn by my example&quot;.<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:32:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> Nope.  I saw them.<br><br>My point is that to dismiss out of hand what players may or may not accomplished or considered before grouping is a dangerous exercise.<br><br>Granted - you, I, and the vast majority of people who care about roleplaying in general - your 90% disengenous figure may be a little conservative... let's say 98%.  But there are a lot of really great stories and storylines that can be overlooked by a blanket eyeroll.<br><br>Swing by the Twilight Bastion boards and read some of the back story that goes on with Cronadan's flight from Neriak ( <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub59.ezboard.com/ftwilightbastionfrm11">pub59.ezboard.com/ftwilightbastionfrm11</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ) or  Isharra's descent into slavery to the Iksar Empire ( <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ).  There are those black swans who put forth the effort and time to make a compelling story about and around their toon, and it's a shame that those few can be easily dismissed because a traditionally evil race is seen hunting ulthorks with a traditionally good one.<br><br>The tragedy in this is that those great efforts on this server are vastly outnumbered by the folks who just want a necro's damage-dealing or a troll's tanking ability in the party.<br><br>There's no excitement in a black and white world... all the good shit happens in the grey area.  Whether that takes the form of a &quot;black sheep&quot; friend, a hidden love affair, or inner conflict within the individual is up to the user.  Living up to archetype is hard work, too... just boring.<br><br>So, I largely agree with you, Lasgalen.  But we're going to differ on what I perceive to be snap judgement.  I wouldn't want to sift through the random crap most people slap together and call a backstory, either, and I don't blame you for not doing it.  However, I just find that the elite few who break the mold WELL give me enough of a lift to look beyond the power-levellers and lewt-hunters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 408<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:35:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Firiona Vie (Convenience Preferred)</span><hr size=1> Awww.... thanks for the compliment, Uinin! <p><br><imgsrc="http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/ISHARR6.jpg"><br><b><br><b>Property of Voskor Oth</b><br><b>Slave to the Iksar Empire</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 679<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:44:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1228.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   